It’s About What You Preserve
Most people believe the legal system is about truth or fairness.

It’s not.

It’s about what gets preserved in the record.

That distinction is everything.

Because in real systems—courts, arbitration, administrative processes—what is not properly preserved may as well never have happened.

THE MISSING SKILL: PROCEDURAL LITERACY

We are taught to argue our position, explain what happened, and defend ourselves.

But we are almost never taught:

- What must be filed
- What must be timed correctly
- What must be structured to survive review

People don’t lose because they are wrong.

They lose because they failed to preserve their position.

